Adjust #rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat #oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}. Dice @sweet potato{1} into ½-inch pieces. Trim and quarter @cremini mushrooms{8%ounce}. Core, deseed, and dice @bell pepper{1} into ½-inch pieces.

== Ginger Rice ==

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in a small #pot over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and @ginger{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4); cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, 1¼ cups water (2¼ cups for 4), and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Roasted Veggies ==

While rice cooks, in a #medium bowl, toss sweet potato and mushrooms with a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon}, half the @hoisin sauce{2%tablespoon} (you'll use the rest later), @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Spread out on one side of a #baking sheet{}.

Toss bell pepper on empty side with a drizzle of oil, salt, and pepper.

> For 4 servings, use 2 sheets; roast sweet potato and mushrooms on top rack and bell pepper on middle rack.

Roast on top rack until veggies are just tender, ~{15%minutes} (they'll finish cooking in next step).

== Sriracha Soy Mayo ==

While veggies roast, in a #small bowl, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @sour cream{2%tablespoon}, @soy sauce{2%tablespoon}, and as much @sriracha{1%teaspoon} as you like.

> TIP: Start with half the Sriracha, then taste and add more from there if you like things spicy.

== Finish and Serve ==

Once veggies have roasted 15 minutes, remove #baking sheet{} from #oven. Using a #spatula, carefully toss sweet potato and mushrooms with remaining hoisin and half the @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon} (save the rest for serving).

Return to oven until veggies are tender and glaze is tacky, ~{5-8%minutes} more.

Fluff rice with a #fork; season with salt.

Divide rice between bowls. Top with sweet potato, mushrooms, and bell pepper. Drizzle with as much Sriracha soy mayo as you like. Garnish with scallion greens and remaining sesame seeds. Serve.